---
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';

const pageTitle = "Sarah's Blog";
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>My Astro Blog</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=VT323&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/global.css">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'VT323', monospace;
            background-color: #00008B; /* Dark Blue */
            color: #00FF00; /* Neon Green */
            background-image: url('https://www.transparenttextures.com/patterns/stardust.png');
            line-height: 1.8;
		}
        .has-sidebar {
            display: flex;
        }
        .sidebar {
            width: 217px;
            background-color: #00008B;
            padding: 2em;
            border-right: 2px solid #f119b1;
            height: 100vh;
            position: fixed;
        }
        .main-content {
            flex: 1;
            padding: 2em;
            margin-left: 290px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="has-sidebar">
    <Header />
    <div class="sidebar">
        <title>{pageTitle}</title>
        <h1>My Astro Blog</h1>
        <p>A chronicle of my journey learning Astro, with a 90s twist!</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="/posts/post-1/">Post 1</a></li>
            <li><a href="/posts/post-2/">Post 2</a></li>
            <li><a href="/posts/post-3/">Post 3</a></li>
          </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="main-content">
        <div class="post">
            <h2 class="post-title">First Post!</h2>
            <p class="post-meta">Published on: 2024-07-25</p>
            <div class="post-content">
                <p>
                    This is my first post on my new Astro-powered blog! I'm excited to explore the world of Astro and document my learning process here. The 90s theme is a fun throwback to the early days of the web. Stay tuned for more updates!
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="/posts/post-1/">Post 1</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="post">
            <h2 class="post-title">Styling with Astro</h2>
            <p class="post-meta">Published on: 2024-07-26</p>
            <div class="post-content">
                <p>
                    Today, I've been diving into how styling works in Astro. It's really flexible! You can use global stylesheets, component-scoped styles, and even import CSS from npm packages. For this blog, I'm using a mix of global styles and some fun, retro-inspired inline styles.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="/posts/post-2/">Post 2</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="post">
            <h2 class="post-title">Creating a Tumblr-Style Layout</h2>
            <p class="post-meta">Published on: 2024-07-27</p>
            <div class="post-content">
                <p>
                    I decided to give my blog a classic Tumblr-style layout. It's a two-column design with a fixed sidebar on the left for the blog title, description, and navigation, and the main content area on the right for the posts. I achieved this using some simple CSS Flexbox. It's amazing how powerful modern CSS is!
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="/posts/post-3/">Post 3</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <Footer />
    <script>
		import "../scripts/menu.js";
	</script>
</body>
</html>
